Write down your observations from above two graphs:¶

observations from numerical hue value and Categorical hue Value :

1. color:¶
  1. For numerical hue:
    • the color is a gradient it gradually increases contrast with increse in the value of the hue Variable.
  2. For Categorical hue:
    • the color for each Value(category) is represented differently.
2. Distribution:¶
  1. For Numerical hue:
    • the distribution of the Scatter for the given Hue value is according to corresponding X and Y values of the axes.
  2. For Categorical hue:
    • the distribution is irrespective of the X and Y values, the data is just grouped into the respective 'Tag' values.

Create a new column with name 'Ans' using Answers column in the df:¶

  • make the values which are 0 as Unanswered
  • make the values which are in 1-20 range as 'Twenty'
  • make the values which are in 21-40 range as 'Forty'
  • make the values which are in 41-60 range as 'Sixty'
  • make the values which are in 61-80 range as 'Eighty' ##### Here You are creating a categorical column from numerical ccolumn
In [24]:
df.loc[(df['Answers']==0),'Ans'] = 'Unanswered'
df.loc[(df['Answers'] >=1) & (df['Answers'] <= 20), 'Ans'] = 'Twenty'
df.loc[(df['Answers'] >=21) & (df['Answers'] <= 40), 'Ans'] = 'Forty'
df.loc[(df['Answers'] >=41) & (df['Answers'] <= 60), 'Ans'] = 'Sixty'
df.loc[(df['Answers'] >=61) & (df['Answers'] <= 80), 'Ans'] = 'Eighty'
